text: Spencer County is a county in the U.S. state of Kentucky. As of the 2020 census, the population was 19,490. Its county seat is Taylorsville. The county was formed in 1824 and named for Kentucky's Captain Spier Spencer, who fought and died in the Battle of Tippecanoe. == References == Category:1820s establishments in Kentucky Category:1824 establishments in the United States Category:Kentucky counties
title: Spencer County, Kentucky
